<!-- ─── Brewer EN ─── -->
<h2 id="brewer-profession">Brewer Profession</h2>
<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Professions are not currently active in v0.9.0.</strong> This data exists in the game files but the feature is likely not yet finished — included here as a curiosity.</div>

<p>Brewer profession benefits:</p>
<ul>
  <li>🧪 Potion brewing (Brewing Stand access)</li>
  <li>🧀 Cheese crafting (from Hardstone Milk Buckets)</li>
  <li>⚗️ Special Cauldron recipes</li>
  <li>💊 Disenchanting Bottle crafting</li>
</ul>

<table>
  <tr><th>Level</th><th>XP Required</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>Basic potions (Strength I, Speed I, Regeneration I...)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>~500 XP</td><td>Potion level II available; more effective splash potions</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>~2000 XP</td><td>Potion level III; extended duration</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>~8000 XP</td><td>Potion level IV (max strength/speed); 5× cheese recipe</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="tip">💡 <strong>Tip:</strong> Brewer and Blacksmith/Enchanter cannot be combined — only 1 profession per character. If you focus on combat, consider whether Enchanter might be more valuable than Brewer for your playstyle.</div>

<!-- ─── Cauldron EN ─── -->
<h2 id="cauldron">Cauldron Mechanics</h2>
<p>The Cauldron isn't just for storing water — it's the source of unique MITE recipes that CANNOT be made in a Brewing Stand.</p>

<div class="info">ℹ️ Craft the Cauldron at an <strong>Iron Workbench</strong> (blacksmithing skill required): 7× Iron Ingots in a U-shape (3×3 grid).</div>

<table>
  <tr><th>Recipe</th><th>Process</th><th>Result</th><th>Use</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong style="color:var(--gold)">Liquid Gold</strong></td>
    <td>Place Cauldron under lava source + throw Gold Ore in → wait 10 seconds</td>
    <td>Liquid gold in cauldron</td>
    <td>Craft 4× Golden Apples from it</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong style="color:var(--silver)">Liquid Mercury</strong></td>
    <td>Mercury ore + Lava in cauldron → smelting process</td>
    <td>Liquid mercury (collect with bucket)</td>
    <td>Alloying ingredient; Ancient Metal Backpack recipe</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong style="color:var(--ancient)">Ancient Metal Backpack</strong></td>
    <td>Leather Backpack + 4× Ancient Metal Ingot in mercury → wait 30 seconds</td>
    <td>Ancient Metal Backpack</td>
    <td>More inventory slots, more durable backpack</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<div class="tip">💡 <strong>Mercury source:</strong> Mercury ore found in Swamp biome (Y 0–40). Requires @3 furnace (Obsidian Furnace) to smelt!</div>

