<!-- ─── Splash EN ─── -->
<h2 id="splash-potions">Splash Potions</h2>
<p>Most potions can be made in Splash form — add <strong>Gunpowder</strong> to any finished potion in the Brewing Stand.</p>

<div class="tip">💡 Splash potions can be thrown at enemies (Instant Damage, Slowness, Weakness) OR allies (Instant Health, Strength). Harming Splash is especially effective against Fire Elementals which are otherwise fire-immune!</div>

<table>
  <tr><th>Strategy</th><th>Potion</th><th>Target</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Boss fight boost</td><td>Strength IV Splash</td><td>Yourself</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Escape</td><td>Speed IV Splash</td><td>Yourself</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Fire Elemental</td><td>Harming Splash</td><td>Enemy (won't hurt you!)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Crowd control</td><td>Poison IV Splash</td><td>Mob groups</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Wounded ally</td><td>Instant Health II Splash</td><td>Partner NPC</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ─── Disenchanting EN ─── -->
<h2 id="disenchanting">Disenchanting Bottle</h2>
<p>A unique MITE potion crafted in the <strong>Brewing Stand</strong> (Brewer required). Recipe: Nether Wart + Coal → Water Bottles.</p>

<BrewingGrid
  ingredient="Nether Wart + Coal"
  ingredientImg="img/items/nether_wart.png"
  inputLabel="Water Bottle × 3"
  inputImg="img/items/glass_bottle.png"
  result="Disenchanting Bottle"
  resultColor="#7ec8e3"
  hu="Varázstalanító Palack"
  en="Disenchanting Bottle"
/>

<p><strong>Effects:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>✅ Remove enchantments from items (XP is recovered!)</li>
  <li>✅ Clear active potion effects from yourself</li>
  <li>✅ Remove witch curses</li>
  <li>⚠️ Does NOT affect item Quality</li>
</ul>

<div class="tip">💡 Extremely useful if you got a bad enchantment at the Enchanting Table, or if a Witch cursed your equipment!</div>

<!-- ─── Cheese EN ─── -->
<h2 id="cheese">Cheese Crafting</h2>
<p><strong>Brewer skill</strong> required. Any milk bucket material works — Hardstone, Copper, Silver, Gold, Iron, Ancient Metal, Mithril, Adamantium. The bucket tier determines which workbench is needed to craft the cheese.</p>

<div class="info">ℹ️ Each cow type requires a matching bucket material to milk. All recipes share the same <strong>6,400 difficulty/unit</strong> regardless of bucket material.</div>

<table>
  <tr><th>Buckets</th><th>Output</th><th>Difficulty/unit</th><th>Efficiency</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1× bucket</td><td>1× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--accent)">6,400</td><td>Base (1×)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2× buckets</td><td>2× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--gold)">3,200/unit</td><td>2× efficient</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3× buckets</td><td>3× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--gold)">2,133/unit</td><td>3× efficient</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4× buckets</td><td>4× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--green)">1,600/unit</td><td>4× efficient</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5× buckets</td><td>5× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--green)">1,280/unit</td><td>5× efficient</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9× buckets</td><td>9× Cheese</td><td style="color:var(--green)">711/unit</td><td style="color:var(--green)">9× efficient (MAX)</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="tip">💡 <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Always use as many buckets as possible — recipes scale up to 9 buckets, and each additional bucket reduces the difficulty-per-unit ratio significantly!</div>

